DECREASE IN XBOX 360 PLATFORM MARKETING. COST OF REVENUE DECREASED $143 MILLION OR 2%, DUE MAINLY TO A $1.0 BILLION DECREASE IN MANUFACTURING AND DISTRIBUTION COSTS ASSOCIATED WITH LOWER VOLUMES

OF XBOX 360 CONSOLES SOLD, OFFSET IN PART BY A $375 MILLION INCREASE IN EXPENSES FOR PAYMENTS MADE TO NOKIA RELATED TO JOINT STRATEGIC INITIATIVES AND A $273 MILLION INCREASE IN ROYALTIES ON XBOX LIVE CONTENT. RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT EXPENSES

