

561 MILLION (APPROXIMATELY $733 MILLION) FOR FAILURE TO COMPLY WITH OUR 2009 AGREEMENT TO DISPLAY A BROWSER CHOICE SCREEN ON

WINDOWS PCS WHERE INTERNET EXPLORER IS THE DEFAULT BROWSER (THE EU FINE). CORPORATE-LEVEL EXPENSES ALSO GREW DUE TO A $350 MILLION INCREASE IN RETAIL STORES EXPENSES AND $287 MILLION HIGHER INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY LICENSING COSTS.

FISCAL YEAR 2012 COMPARED WITH FISCAL YEAR 2011

CORPORATE-LEVEL EXPENSES INCREASED DUE MAINLY TO FULL YEAR PUERTO RICAN EXCISE TAXES, HIGHER HEADCOUNT-RELATED EXPENSES, AND CHANGES IN FOREIGN CURRENCY EXCHANGE RATES. THESE INCREASES WERE OFFSET IN PART BY LOWER

LEGAL CHARGES, WHICH WERE $56 MILLION IN FISCAL YEAR 2012 COMPARED WITH $332 MILLION IN FISCAL YEAR 2011.

