GOODWILL IMPAIRMENT

WE TEST GOODWILL FOR IMPAIRMENT ANNUALLY ON MAY 1 AT THE REPORTING UNIT LEVEL USING A FAIR VALUE APPROACH. NO IMPAIRMENT OF GOODWILL WAS

IDENTIFIED AS OF MAY 1, 2013. OUR GOODWILL IMPAIRMENT TEST AS OF MAY 1, 2012, INDICATED THAT OSDS CARRYING VALUE EXCEEDED ITS ESTIMATED FAIR VALUE. ACCORDINGLY, WE RECORDED A NON-CASH, NON-TAX DEDUCTIBLE GOODWILL IMPAIRMENT CHARGE OF

$6.2 BILLION DURING THE THREE MONTHS ENDED JUNE 30, 2012, REDUCING OSDS GOODWILL FROM $6.4 BILLION TO $223 MILLION.

